public class java_51702_SessionManager_A08 {   // Class name should start with uppercase letter. For naming convention, camel case is a good choice. Hence I named it as 'MySession'. Please be creative and realistic about your code! :)
    private static int counter = 0;     // A simple integer to identify each session created by our program (optional). 
                                        // This could act like an ID for the user, or other means of identifying a unique entity. Be specific in what you name it as per requirement and comment accordingly about its usage/purpose within your project context!  
    private boolean isValid = false;     // A session should always be valid before any operations are performed on them (optional).  If not set to true, the operation could potentially result in a integrity failure. This field can help you manage sessions effectively and protect against potential errors or attacks like SQL Injection etc!
    private String id;                   // Unique identifier for each session - this should be generated when it's created (optional).  It might act as an authentication token, user ID among others depending on the requirements of your program. Be specific about its usage in project context and comment accordingly if required or not applicable!
    
    public java_51702_SessionManager_A08() {                  // Constructor for a new session - optional but recommended to create sessions properly (optional).  This should generate an unique id when it's created, ensuring that each instance is truly different. Be specific about its usage in project context and comment accordingly if required or not applicable!  
        counter++;                        // Increase the static count for creating new session by one every time this constructor gets called (optional). This can be used to ensure all sessions have unique ids, ensuring integrity of data stored on database. Be specific about its usage in project context and comment accordingly if required or not applicable!  
        setId(Integer.toString(counter)); // Set the default session identifier - optional but recommended for more realistic use-cases (optional).  This will allow us to have each instance behave like a unique user, ensuring security by preventing unauthorized access from being accessed inappropriately within your program! Be specific about its usage and comment accordingly.
    }   // End of MySession constructor
    
    public void setId(String id) {       // Method for setting session identifier (optional). This is often used to authenticate users, or other means if you want sessions not just tracked around program flow like in a multi-thread environment etc. Be specific about its usage and comment accordingly!  
        this.id = id;                      // Set the provided string as new unique ID for session (optional). This could be used to authenticate users, or other means if you want sessions not just tracked around program flow like in a multi-thread environment etc. Be specific about its usage and comment accordingly! 
    }   // End of setId method     
    
}                                  // Session management can always fail when trying operations on session that are invalid (for example, already closed), so we need to ensure our sessions behave this way in a robust manner with error handling. Use the 'isValid' field above for checking and validating if your current operation is legal or not!